sec.p:
XRD patterns of pure MgB2, Co-doped MgB2, and Fe-doped MgB2 are illustrated in Fig. 1. For comparison, the theoretical diffraction pattern of magnesium diboride has also been included40,42. Reflections shown in the theoretical pattern have appeared in both undoped MgB2 as well as Mg1−xTMxB2 which confirms the successful synthesis technique applied in this study. However, there are trace amounts of labeled intrinsic impurities such as MgO (marked by #) at 2θ of 36.7°, 62.38° and Mg (marked by *) at 32.28°, 34.52°, 47.86°. Based on the literature40, two main paths that lead to the formation of MgO are as follows. 
If Mg precursor powder is sintered under oxygen it will produce MgO according to the following reaction:2Mgs+O2g→2MgOs\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
